No, that's not necessary, but they are lined with something...not just raw leather, correct?  Some other makers do not line at all.

Hi I do have a question about the types of nylon. I am looking for a very thin ripstop fabric that would be good to use on a very light weight synthetic jacket. My hopes would be that this fabric would be quiet in compared with some nylons that almost sound like plastic bags when crinkled or rubbed together. Do you have any suggestions on fabric or weight of fabric I should look for?
The first thing I recommend is that you order a sample pack to make sure the fabric meets all your needs, but I think our HyperD 1.0 would be perfect for you.  It's very soft, and makes no crinkle.
Ok if we were to place an order this morning how fast would we receive the order?
Our typical in house lead time is 1 business day, and we ship via priority mail which is 2-3 days depending on your location in the country.
Ok great, so if we were to place the order this morning would it ship tomorrow?
Ok, I think The hyperD is one we will want to test around with, do you have any other suggestions on other samples to try?
Also is the Hyper D fabric a breathable fabric?
Yes, the HyperD is breathable, were you specifically looking for a waterproof material?
I would say water resistant not waterproof
Has this fabric been treated with DWR?
I would order a sample of the calendared and uncalendared versions of HyperD 1.0, 1.1 Calendared ripstop, and try a piece of .66 Membrane10.
Calendared fabrics will give you more wind and water resistance over the uncalendared versions
So the calendared has been treated with DWR and the uncalendared has not been?

They've both been treated, but the calendared fabrics go through an addition heat treatment to seal up the gaps between threads (for downproofness)  this makes them more water and wind resistant as a result.
ok interesting. So would you generally recomend a calendered version for a light weight jacket?
Yes, especially where wind resistance is wanted.

Hi, Im sorry I missed your chat.
The regular clay mask and the hydrated clay mask are the same thing.  We've been doing this so long we interchange the names of our clay mask and confuse people.  :)
The mask for the face is the 100% pure magnesium bentonite clay.  IT's a hydrated clay mask.  Which mean you don't have to mix it.
Yes.  The powered is the same, but you have to mix it?

The powdered is the same type of clay as the hydrated, but mixing it yourself will sometimes end up in a lumpy consistency.  Though the effect will be the same.  Just not as pretty as the hydrated clay.   I recommend buying it pre-mixed in the hydrated form.
Can you tell me about the soap?  Is it okay to use with combination skin?
The soap is a wonderful face wash.  You can use it for the body as well. One bar last a long time for the face.
Great for combination skin. oily skin.  dry skin.  all skin types.
We even use the soap for babies with eczema.
Is it a good soap to use for when you get a scratch (say from a cat or a tree branch)?  Like to clean the area before you apply a Neosporin type cream?
It cleanses the area really well. So, yes.  It would be a good soap for post-cat rescue scratches :)

so I was in a relationship (long distance) to a childhood sweetheart.  This relationship picked up fast where I was going to relocate to be with him.  Recently he called it off because of communication problems.  I swear, If I told you what he said you would be confused too.  I'm really trying to get past the hurt and wanted to see if it's worth fighting for.
I hope you plan on buying some of my tees! lol!
i do.  I love the purpose over paper
People ask all these questions and want answers, but don't understand I actually have stuff to do. lol!
What color of Purpose Over Paper are you getting? Just curious?
you only seem to have black
guess not.... I just checked the other colors...
I'll make a deal with you. You get the black and I'll drop some sweet science on this subject in a way that will resonate with your soul.
I'm actually writing and preparing it now. It won't be long and boring. It will be to the point, but you will get it.
It got a lot longer than I was anticipating. lol!!

Here's a little known fact. "A man who wants to be with you will build bridges to get to you." A man who does not want to be with you is often wanting something that you are not. He may never say this, but it is true. He can blame it on all kinds of things but in the end, you are not what he wants. Sometimes, you're not what he wants at that time! So, you're job is to accept that you cannot control his desires. You cannot become what he wants you to be. If you try to do that, you'll lose touch with your identity and you will eventually become very resentful. It's like pretending to like threesomes, just so you can be with the man you "love."  I say "threesomes" because that is exactly what it is; you, him and the person you're pretending to be. Whenever you encounter situations like this, your immediate focus should be "YOU." Will it hurt? Yes it will. But, that's the way life is. However, every window of pain and loss is actually an opportunity for you to become better. By "better" I do not mean richer, slimmer, or more fashion conscious. I mean better in the way you love yourself , your friends and family.  Better in the way you choose who enters your circle. Because whether you're willing to admit this or not, you've always known something between you and him was slightly off. So, the only person you can fault is yourself. You allowed it to happen the way that it did. You are not a victim. You are not seeking revenge. You are seeking a peace of mind and a better understanding of why you allowed yourself to be in this long distance, semi relationship to begin with. Maybe, you're attracted to men who are emotionally unavailable.  Maybe, you feel safer dating someone you've known a lifetime. The bottom line is, your job is to focus on you and figure out why you accepted things the way they were. What in your psyche allows you to accept such things? You will get better. You will overcome your pain and you will be extremely happy you allowed the man who truly loves you, to fight for YOU.

He never wanted to leave Antigua because his kids lives with him and made ok money.  He didn't feel like it made sense to move here to struggle.  I get it, so I compromised being down there instead.  But now that I went for three  months to spend time, it didn't seem to mesh.  Yes, I take blame because I wanted it to work so bad I ignored important signs.  My ex husband did have communication issues (Trinidadian)
and my father was also broken.  Wow, now I see that I like broken people.. lol
but on the serious side, I need to change this trend.

All good... I will leave you with this: You're talking with family now. You are an insightful being with experience. You knew all along and chose to ignore important signs. You are wise to take responsibility.  Compromising is a part of life. But what's the point of compromising with someone who isn't invested in the first place? I have no doubt in  my mind that YOU will be fine. Not everyone can come to the realizations that you're coming to so quickly. We're all broken. The difference is, YOU don't want to be with anyone who is in denial of that. YOU want to be with someone who is aware and willing to take responsibility for their own shit. Therapy did wonders for me. Solitude did wonders for me. Mediation did wonders for me.

column17: Hello i was wondering if i could ask for some advice?

column9: Hi, of course. What can I help you with?

Last may i was signed off work due to a bad back injury which built up over time due to being understaffed and over worked by upper management, in october my contract was terminated due to us not being able to agree on a return to work date, my injury is as bad as ever
I have had mri, xray and blood tests and also physiotherapy and still haven't got answers
Right, okay could I ask, what type of work you were doing and how long you were employed there?
I was a department manager on produce for morrisons, and worked there for 5 years
Okay, and how do you think the back injury was caused? Lifting heavy weights, tasks that involve awkward postures etc.
Yes heavy lifting was a factor but also was the nature of my work, it was being overworked and doing 2-3 peoples jobs in one shift
I see, so am I right in thinking that at some point over the 5 years your employer reduced the amount of staff on your department but the workload remained the same?
Yes it was sometimes down to less staff and other times sickness on the department
Okay, this may be a tricky question to answer but do you have an idea of the weights you were lifting and how often you would be moving/lifting these weights a day?

Hmm I'm not sure of an exact weight but pallets would come in on delivery and would have fruit and veg in trays, a bag of potatoes could weigh up to 2.5kg and have 7 bags in one tray, this would be a daily thing due to our night crew being taken away
4am starts, on days like friday and saturday there be up to 18 pallets of stock all with around 30-50 trays on each pallet. Upper management would expect this done by one person by 7am
Admittedly it wasn't always me on these 4am starts but i did at least 3 a week, with 9 night shifts in a row leading up to christmas 2015

Right, thank you for providing me with all this information it is really helping to develop a clear picture of what has happened. It does appear that there could be something in this as the weights are relatively heavy and you are doing an awful lot of lifting and moving. Would you be willing to have a chat over the phone to establish a few more details?
From there we can advise of the best course of action and whether or not you have a claim. It should not take more than 10-15 minutes.
I can't talk on the phone right now because i cannot receive incoming calls, i know that's a pain
Okay, that's not a problem. May I ask you a few more questions then? I will then be able to speak with one of our specialist back solicitors and get back to you via email
This injury has me in high levels of pain every day as pain medication doesn't work, i lost my job, my social life and my freedom to be honest.....yes sure you can ask more questions
Okay, what happened when you tried to return to work? Did your employer agree to put you on lighter duties or change your job role at all?

I didn't try to return, I didn't feel able to. I met with occupational health and told them what was happening, i met with my employer and we agreed to terminate contract because I couldn't tell them when i would be fit again
Which as an employer i understand that's what they have to do
Okay, I understand. Did your employer assist you when the injury first occurred?
Well i worked for a couple of weeks with my back in a bad way and it was more my staff on dept helping me rather than the upper management, i was still asked to do a lot of lifting and bending
Which is ultimately why i went to the doctors for their advice

Right, i think i have enough information here at this stage. We would ideally need to speak you over the phone at some point to establish some other details. Would that be possible in the next week or so?
Do you think i have grounds for a claim or am i just thinking too much into it? And this thing just happens in retail?

You are 100% right to have this looked into, based on what you have said to me their maybe grounds for a claim but it is difficult to say without going into this a bit more which is why we would need to have a quick chat on the phone. Could i take your name and contact number please?
Sure my name is Dan Bailey and my number is 07411264392
people have been telling me to seek advice but I didn't think i could due to it not being one specific moment where i injured my back
Thanks Dan. It is also worth seeking advice and there is no harm done if it doesn't lead to anything. There are many ways a back injury can be caused from work and your case is one of them.

I will arrange for a specialist to call you on Tuesday and run through your case and see if we can take this on for you. You are not obligated to anything at all and all our cases our no win, no fee if we do decide to run this for you
Is there a specific time on Tuesday you would like us to call you?
Ok great, thanks for the help. Around lunch time will be fine
No problem, lunch time sounds fine. We will speak with you then, thanks for your time today Dan
Thank you again speak to you soon
